The paper deals with machine learning and focuses on loss functions, empirical risk, and generalization bounds. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses weakly supervised learning and label noise robustness, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses mathematical and statistical techniques to prove its results, which suggests that it could also be relevant to sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
